.TH "drm_dp_mst_atomic_enable_dsc" 9 "drm_dp_mst_atomic_enable_dsc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dp_mst_atomic_enable_dsc \- Set DSC Enable Flag to On/Off
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_dp_mst_atomic_enable_dsc
.BI "(struct drm_atomic_state *state "  ","
.BI "struct drm_dp_mst_port *port "  ","
.BI "int pbn "  ","
.BI "int pbn_div "  ","
.BI "bool enable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
Pointer to the new drm_atomic_state
.IP "port" 12
Pointer to the affected MST Port
.IP "pbn" 12
Newly recalculated bw required for link with DSC enabled
.IP "pbn_div" 12
Divider to calculate correct number of pbn per slot
.IP "enable" 12
Boolean flag to enable or disable DSC on the port
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function enables DSC on the given Port
by recalculating its vcpi from pbn provided
and sets dsc_enable flag to keep track of which
ports have DSC enabled
